    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Agents Need Explicit Data Handling Rules"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agentic systems are persistent, multi-tool, and multi-turn. Unlike a stateless API call that processes one request and discards its inputs, an agent may retain sensitive data across turns, carry it through tool calls, embed it in sub-agent prompts, and surface it in logs. Without explicit handling rules at each stage of the data lifecycle, a piece of personally identifiable information (PII) ingested in turn 1 can leak through a webhook call in turn 7 \u2014 long after the user assumed it was gone."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The data lifecycle approach treats sensitive data as something that must be "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "classified",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "labeled",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "minimised",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "disposed of",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " systematically \u2014 not just blocked at the output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Four-Phase Lifecycle"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Sensitive Data Lifecycle \u2014 four phases: ingest, in-context use, output/tool, disposal",
          "title": "Sensitive Data Lifecycle \u2014 four phases: ingest, in-context use, output/tool, disposal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 1: Classification and Ingestion"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every piece of data that enters the agent pipeline should be classified at the point of ingestion \u2014 before it reaches the LLM context. Classification drives all downstream decisions: whether to redact, tokenise, or restrict the data."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Flag, auto\nimport re\n\nclass Sensitivity(Flag):\n    NONE        = 0\n    PII         = auto()   # name, email, phone, address, DOB\n    FINANCIAL   = auto()   # card number, bank account, salary\n    CREDENTIAL  = auto()   # password, API key, token, private key\n    HEALTH      = auto()   # diagnosis, medication, medical record\n    INTERNAL    = auto()   # confidential business data, trade secrets\n\n# Pattern-based classifiers (supplement with a trained model for production)\nCLASSIFICATION_PATTERNS: list[tuple[Sensitivity, re.Pattern]] = [\n    (Sensitivity.PII, re.compile(\n        r\"\\b[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Z|a-z]{2,}\\b\")),           # email\n    (Sensitivity.PII, re.compile(\n        r\"\\b(\\+?1[-\\s.]?)?\\(?\\d{3}\\)?[-\\s.]\\d{3}[-\\s.]\\d{4}\\b\")),    # US phone\n    (Sensitivity.PII, re.compile(\n        r\"\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b\")),                                          # SSN\n    (Sensitivity.FINANCIAL, re.compile(\n        r\"\\b(?:4[0-9]{12}(?:[0-9]{3})?|5[1-5][0-9]{14}|3[47][0-9]{13})\\b\")),  # credit card\n    (Sensitivity.CREDENTIAL, re.compile(\n        r\"(api.?key|secret|password|token|private.?key).{0,30}[:=]\", re.I)),\n    (Sensitivity.HEALTH, re.compile(\n        r\"\\b(diagnosis|icd-?10|medication|prescription|patient.?id)\\b\", re.I)),\n]\n\ndef classify(text: str) -> Sensitivity:\n    result = Sensitivity.NONE\n    for sensitivity, pattern in CLASSIFICATION_PATTERNS:\n        if pattern.search(text):\n            result |= sensitivity\n    return result"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Redaction and Tokenisation at Ingestion"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once classified, sensitive values are either redacted (replaced with a placeholder) or tokenised (replaced with a reversible opaque token) before the LLM sees them. Tokenisation is preferred when the agent needs to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "reference",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the data later \u2014 for example, to pass a customer ID back to a database lookup \u2014 but does not need to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "reason about",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " its raw value."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import secrets, hashlib\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n@dataclass\nclass TokenVault:\n    \"\"\"Maps random tokens to real values within one session.\"\"\"\n    _store: dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict, init=False)\n\n    def tokenise(self, value: str, prefix: str = \"tok\") -> str:\n        token = f\"{prefix}_{secrets.token_hex(8)}\"\n        self._store[token] = value\n        return token\n\n    def detokenise(self, token: str) -> str:\n        if token not in self._store:\n            raise KeyError(f\"Unknown token: {token!r}\")\n        return self._store[token]\n\n    def purge(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Call at session end to destroy all token\u2194value mappings.\"\"\"\n        self._store.clear()\n\n# Redaction \u2014 used when the value is not needed by the agent at all\nPII_REDACT_PATTERNS = [\n    (re.compile(r\"\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b\"), \"[SSN REDACTED]\"),\n    (re.compile(r\"\\b(?:4[0-9]{12}(?:[0-9]{3})?)\\b\"), \"[CARD REDACTED]\"),\n    (re.compile(r\"\\b[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Z|a-z]{2,}\\b\"), \"[EMAIL REDACTED]\"),\n]\n\ndef redact(text: str) -> str:\n    for pattern, replacement in PII_REDACT_PATTERNS:\n        text = pattern.sub(replacement, text)\n    return text\n\n# Combined ingestion step\ndef ingest_user_message(text: str, vault: TokenVault) -> tuple[str, Sensitivity]:\n    sensitivity = classify(text)\n    if Sensitivity.CREDENTIAL in sensitivity or Sensitivity.FINANCIAL in sensitivity:\n        # Tokenise \u2014 agent may need to reference the value\n        import re as _re\n        for pattern, _ in CLASSIFICATION_PATTERNS:\n            for m in pattern.finditer(text):\n                token = vault.tokenise(m.group(0))\n                text = text.replace(m.group(0), token, 1)\n    elif Sensitivity.PII in sensitivity:\n        text = redact(text)\n    return text, sensitivity"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 2: In-Context Use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once data enters the LLM context it is replicated into every subsequent token \u2014 into the model's KV cache, into log entries if the conversation is stored, and into any sub-agent prompt that receives the context. The rules for in-context use are therefore about "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "minimisation",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "scope containment",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Minimum necessary context:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " pass only the fields the agent needs. If a task requires knowing the user's city but not their full address, pass only the city."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No raw logging:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " conversation logs must apply the same redaction as the ingestion step. Log the redacted form, not the original."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Session scoping:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " sensitive values in an agent's memory store must be tagged with the session ID and auto-expired when the session closes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Taint propagation:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when a tainted value is used to construct a new string or document, the result inherits the sensitivity label."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Flag, auto\n\n@dataclass\nclass ContextEntry:\n    key: str\n    value: str\n    sensitivity: Sensitivity\n    session_id: str\n    expires_at: float          # unix timestamp\n\nclass SessionScopedContext:\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str, ttl_seconds: float = 3600):\n        self._session_id = session_id\n        self._ttl = ttl_seconds\n        self._entries: dict[str, ContextEntry] = {}\n\n    def put(self, key: str, value: str, sensitivity: Sensitivity) -> None:\n        import time\n        self._entries[key] = ContextEntry(\n            key=key,\n            value=value,\n            sensitivity=sensitivity,\n            session_id=self._session_id,\n            expires_at=time.time() + self._ttl,\n        )\n\n    def get(self, key: str) -> ContextEntry:\n        import time\n        entry = self._entries.get(key)\n        if entry is None:\n            raise KeyError(key)\n        if time.time() > entry.expires_at:\n            del self._entries[key]\n            raise KeyError(f\"Context entry '{key}' has expired\")\n        return entry\n\n    def purge_session(self) -> None:\n        self._entries.clear()\n\n    def log_safe_summary(self) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Returns a log-safe dict \u2014 values replaced with sensitivity labels.\"\"\"\n        return {\n            k: f\"[{v.sensitivity.name}]\"\n            for k, v in self._entries.items()\n            if v.sensitivity != Sensitivity.NONE\n        }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 3: Output and Tool Arguments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The output phase is where sensitive data most often leaks. The agent may include a token or redacted value in its text response, pass a raw value as a tool argument, or inadvertently embed a credential in a log message it writes. The two controls for this phase are "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "de-tokenisation in place",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (only reveal the real value where strictly necessary) and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pre-send scanning",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (check all outbound content against sensitivity patterns before any I/O)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re\n\nTOKEN_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"\\btok_[0-9a-f]{16}\\b\")\n\ndef detokenise_response(text: str, vault: TokenVault) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Replace tokens in agent response with real values for authorised output.\"\"\"\n    def replace(m: re.Match) -> str:\n        try:\n            return vault.detokenise(m.group(0))\n        except KeyError:\n            return m.group(0)  # unknown token \u2014 leave as-is\n    return TOKEN_PATTERN.sub(replace, text)\n\ndef scan_before_send(content: str, sensitivity: Sensitivity) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns True (safe to send) only if no sensitive patterns are present\n    in the outbound content.\n    Used for both text responses and tool call argument values.\n    \"\"\"\n    if Sensitivity.CREDENTIAL in sensitivity:\n        for _, pattern in CLASSIFICATION_PATTERNS:\n            if pattern.search(content):\n                return False  # raw credential in output \u2014 block\n    # PII check: ensure any PII is in its redacted / tokenised form\n    for pattern, _ in PII_REDACT_PATTERNS:\n        if pattern.search(content):\n            return False  # raw PII escaped the ingestion redactor\n    return True"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 4: Disposal"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a session ends, all in-memory sensitive values must be explicitly purged. Python's garbage collector does not guarantee when objects are freed, and language models may cache conversation state. Disposal must be "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "explicit",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "audited",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import os, ctypes\n\ndef secure_delete_string(s: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Best-effort in-memory zeroing of a string's bytes.\n    Python strings are immutable and interned, so this is not cryptographically\n    guaranteed \u2014 use a bytearray for credentials that require true secure deletion.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Encode to bytearray for mutable zeroing\n    b = bytearray(s.encode())\n    for i in range(len(b)):\n        b[i] = 0\n\ndef secure_delete_file(path: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Overwrite then unlink \u2014 prevents recovery from storage.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        size = os.path.getsize(path)\n        with open(path, \"r+b\") as f:\n            f.write(b\"\\x00\" * size)\n            f.flush()\n            os.fsync(f.fileno())\n    finally:\n        os.unlink(path)\n\nclass AgentSession:\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.context = SessionScopedContext(session_id)\n        self.vault = TokenVault()\n        self._temp_files: list[str] = []\n\n    def register_temp_file(self, path: str) -> None:\n        self._temp_files.append(path)\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Dispose of all sensitive material. Call in a finally block.\"\"\"\n        self.vault.purge()\n        self.context.purge_session()\n        for path in self._temp_files:\n            try:\n                secure_delete_file(path)\n            except FileNotFoundError:\n                pass\n        self._temp_files.clear()\n        _audit_log(\"SESSION_CLOSED\", session_id=self.session_id)\n\n# Usage pattern\nsession = AgentSession(\"sess-abc123\")\ntry:\n    # ... run agent pipeline ...\n    pass\nfinally:\n    session.close()  # always runs, even on exception"
          }
        ]
      },
